Importantly, the VirusTotal analysis results show that none of the antivirus engines detected the file as malicious; all categorized it as 'undetected,' and only the DAS-Security Orcas Sandbox provided a verdict of 'harmless.' This absence of malicious classification suggests that the file isn't known to belong to any malware family.

Regarding detection statistics, all antivirus engines did not find this file to be malicious. No indicators of compromise (IOCs), such as URLs, IPs, or domains linked to command and control (C2) activities, were identified. Furthermore, there are no known YARA rules or signatures pointing to any malware family. Sandbox results show zero suspicious activity like persistence mechanisms or attempts at network communication encryption. No discussions within the community have flagged this file as a threat thus far. Given its seemingly harmless nature, countermeasures or specific MITRE ATT&CK tactics/techniques are not applicable. However, maintaining up-to-date software with the latest security patches is advised as a proactive safety measure. No mitigation steps are necessary since the file is currently understood to be benign.
